{
  "texts": [
    "Graph Structure Fig.",
    "Types of Graphs Knowledge graphs An array of triples in the form of (h, r, t) or (s, r, o) can be represented as a Knowledge Graph (KG), which is a network of entity nodes and relationship edges, with each triple (h, r, t) representing a single entity node.",
    "The relationship between an entity's head (h) and tail (t) is denoted by the r. Knowledge Graph can be considered a heterogeneous graph from this perspective.",
    "The Knowledge Graph visually depicts several real-world objects and their relationships [32].",
    "It can be used for many new aspects, including information retrieval, knowledge-guided innovation, and answering questions [30]."
  ]
}